==English==
=== Noun ===
'''fugue''' ([[fugues]])

# A [[contrapuntal]] piece of music wherein a particular [[melody]] is played in a number of [[Voice|voices]].  At the beginning of the piece, each voice is introduced in turn by playing the melody, after which it consists of a mix of [[Counter-melody|counter-melodies]], accompaniment passages, periods of [[rest]], and returns to the main melody (often [[Transform|transformed]] in some way).
# Anything in literature, poetry, film, painting, etc., that resembles a fugue in structure or in its elaborate complexity and formality.

